Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.18,0:00:03.98,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(280,0)\pos(364,389)}Ceske Orpbaoage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.01,0:00:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(365,466)}Goodness gracious, you're so...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.68,0:00:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times must you pretend to\Nrun away before you're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.39,0:00:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do it again, you won't get dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.68,0:00:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hear me, Milos?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.10,0:00:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.27,0:00:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take your hands out of your pockets\Nwhen talking to someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.35,0:00:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.11,0:00:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.19,0:00:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was that blonde girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.11,0:00:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw her on Dominican Street, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.20,0:00:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she lives around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.03,0:00:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you keep following her?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.12,0:00:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.25,0:00:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In that case, let's find out where she lives...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.83,0:00:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and report her to the police.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.54,0:00:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And tell them that Mr. Grimmer didn't kill the director{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.09,0:00:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll prove his innocence.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.63,0:00:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Prove his innocence?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.67,0:00:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then Mr Grimmer will be off the hook.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.38,0:00:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.47,0:00:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll hold a meeting to come up with a plan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.76,0:00:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Milos, hurry up and finish your dinner already.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.26,0:02:37.72,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(246,200)\pos(364,353)}The Cruelest Thing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the unlicensed orphanage where it first started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.79,0:02:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The former director of Kinderheim 511\Nwas murdered by someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.83,0:02:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kids said that a blonde girl walked\Nthem right after it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.26,0:02:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He restarted his experiment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the one at Kinderheim 511...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this one was to determine the\Neffects of love on the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we go in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.69,0:03:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police should have already removed any evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.86,0:03:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.73,0:03:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Policeman, Mr. Grimmer is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Detective, the blonde girl is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.08,0:03:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's those kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.83,0:03:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kids from this orphanage must have\Ncome back and put these notes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.09,0:03:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"To Mr. Grimmer."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.22,0:03:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milan Boucek.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.84,0:03:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a famous soccer player's card.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.39,0:03:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be something precious to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I react?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.56,0:03:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this type of situation, what should I feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.53,0:03:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My emotions were stolen by Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:04:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I went to a special school\Nto learn how to express emotions...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But these types of situations are\Nthe most difficult to handle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of expression would be appropriate here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about paying those kids a visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:18.26,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(319,381)}St. Bardejov Orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.26,0:04:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.31,0:04:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always hear a lot about you from the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.39,0:04:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They went out to play and haven't returned yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they come back soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.57,0:04:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.40,0:04:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the children's diary...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.20,0:04:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it looks more like letters addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.87,0:04:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr. Grimmer, let s play soccer again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.33,0:04:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr. Grimmer is bad at soccer, so\NI'll teach him how to get better."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.62,0:04:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr. Grimmer, come play with us again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm smiling now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned how to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned how to make a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually part of those kids' memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.90,0:05:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they think of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they all like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.33,0:05:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what kinds of emotions I should've felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when my own child was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I cry in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.71,0:05:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much should I cry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I scream at the top of my lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.97,0:05:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I clench my teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I still don't know how I should have reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.86,0:05:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.49,0:05:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Antonin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.15,0:06:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.95,0:06:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Antonin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.53,0:06:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just got a message from the Ceske Orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.12,0:06:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something bad happened...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.12,0:06:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down and tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.21,0:06:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found the blonde girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.46,0:06:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, we went looking for\Nher to find out where she lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.63,0:06:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Milos...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milos disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.12,0:06:30.16,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(304,200)\pos(319,380)}Krumlov National Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.31,0:06:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people who came to visit you were...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.65,0:06:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a middle-aged gentleman...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.57,0:06:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a tall German...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.23,0:06:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a Japanese man with long hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.78,0:06:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.49,0:06:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, wasn't there one more person you've left out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.87,0:06:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the nurse, there was a woman with\Nlong blonde hair who also came to visit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, a woman didn't come to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.92,0:07:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the nurse was sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.63,0:07:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very beautiful woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.64,0:07:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.31,0:07:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was actually a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.23,0:07:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milos.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.53,0:07:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have we met somewhere before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.82,0:07:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.53,0:07:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.53,0:07:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.95,0:07:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You come around here a lot, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.83,0:07:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you looking for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.26,0:07:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not come over here and have a seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.93,0:07:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some juice for you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... Are you moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.19,0:07:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a big bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.77,0:08:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.12,0:08:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does your mother live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.83,0:08:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.70,0:08:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say you were looking for your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.92,0:08:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.25,0:08:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know if she actually lives around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how are you going to find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.42,0:08:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a picture of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.47,0:08:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.26,0:08:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you don't know what she looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.97,0:08:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I see her, I'll recognize her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody at the orphanage believes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.52,0:08:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all say there's no way I'd know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.35,0:08:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'll recognize my mom when I see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.23,0:08:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom will recognize me when she sees me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.04,0:08:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she pretends that she doesn't\Nrecognize you when she sees you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.71,0:09:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you born because you were wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.51,0:09:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you abandoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.72,0:09:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't your mother abandon you\Nbecause she didn't like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.18,0:09:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.31,0:09:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being born really isn't that uncommon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.69,0:09:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.94,0:09:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost everything in this world is meant to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this world, a life born is nothing\Nmore than an insignificant speck...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.41,0:09:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shouldn't even be counted as an existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.24,0:09:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Death is natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.75,0:09:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.25,0:09:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because someone wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.38,0:09:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your reason for living?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.81,0:09:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl with long blonde hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.98,0:10:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that would be Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.82,0:10:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does this Anna live around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm pretty sure her apartment\Nis in the alley two blocks down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.87,0:10:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she's such a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.25,0:10:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So polite, she never fails to greet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.50,0:10:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she's such a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Always has a smile when she speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what floor and room she lives in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Third floor, that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If what the kids say is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if Milos was really kidnapped by that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.19,0:10:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that Anna girl is really her, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.99,0:10:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then if that person is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.45,0:10:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything will end here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.68,0:11:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got away already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.76,0:11:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Milos go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.31,0:11:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was he kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was following the blonde girl\Nin order to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.99,0:11:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do now, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.66,0:11:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What expression should I make in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.00,0:11:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kids got dragged into this case because\Nthey wanted to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.25,0:11:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kids told us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.59,0:11:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Milos usually wanders the streets of Prague...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:11:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looking for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.47,0:12:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted... to meet his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.55,0:12:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... felt nothing, even when my own child died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.94,0:12:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, back when I was still\Nworking for the newspapers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.69,0:12:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a female colleague told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she liked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I married her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I was taught that you're less\Nlikely to be suspected as a spy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you're married.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She got pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gave birth to a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then one day, my wife was out shopping nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.30,0:12:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I entered my son's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was lying face down and had stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.18,0:12:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave him CPR...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.60,0:12:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and called the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.22,0:12:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did everything I knew I should do, without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.69,0:12:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he still died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:13:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the funeral, my wife broke down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.07,0:13:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"How can you remain so calm?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why can't you cry?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.37,0:13:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're always like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.99,0:13:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's how you treat me, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.12,0:13:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're unable to love another person."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.25,0:13:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's nothing in your heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.04,0:13:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then my wife left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to find Milos!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.89,0:13:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said Milos was the child of a prostitute\Nin the red-light district...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.85,0:13:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,near the Czech border, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.43,0:13:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.77,0:13:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the person who was living here is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.36,0:13:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he'll let the boy live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.49,0:13:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he won't simply kill the boy either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that person is who I think he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he'll put the boy through the cruelest thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.00,0:13:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.13,0:14:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep going down this road, you'll be in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.42,0:14:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my mom is somewhere down this road?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.63,0:14:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a very lively place up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be able to see my mom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.39,0:14:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.47,0:14:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be able to recognize your mother when you see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.85,0:14:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your mom will recognize you when she sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if no one calls out to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.44,0:14:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that means nobody wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.04,0:14:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.71,0:14:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.00,0:15:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cruel, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.44,0:15:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.32,0:15:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.32,0:15:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.95,0:15:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.29,0:15:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:15:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.87,0:16:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.29,0:16:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.55,0:16:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.38,0:16:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Technically, I know like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.68,0:16:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fifty of them here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why were you abandoned?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.48,0:16:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.77,0:16:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.91,0:16:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, I'm looking for my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.24,0:16:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that, just let me hold you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.79,0:16:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that's your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.75,0:16:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.55,0:16:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't screw up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.51,0:16:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're infected...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.18,0:16:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.68,0:17:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.69,0:17:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already paid you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.06,0:17:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.48,0:17:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do what your customer tells you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.15,0:17:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.78,0:17:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A kid's watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.79,0:17:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a teacher in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At my school, I have a good reputation with the parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.84,0:17:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an honorable man, and a wonderful teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.76,0:17:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wonderful teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.52,0:17:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.19,0:17:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.78,0:17:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.61,0:17:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sick, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.45,0:17:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.66,0:17:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.20,0:17:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just told you, because I'm gonna die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.12,0:18:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.46,0:18:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only have this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Almost everything in this world is meant to die.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is your reason for living?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.09,0:18:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The red-light district ends around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.27,0:19:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of people saw Milos in the district.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we turn back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may still be in there somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.75,0:19:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milos!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.72,0:19:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milos...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.64,0:19:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.73,0:19:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.64,0:19:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.23,0:19:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to prove my innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.90,0:19:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tried your best, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.05,0:20:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this how I'm supposed to feel, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be better if I cried?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.61,0:20:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was never taught...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.19,0:20:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,such complicated feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Milos?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.56,0:21:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.43,0:21:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.15,0:21:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milos, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.78,0:21:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There {\i1}is{\i0} a reason why you were born!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.00,0:21:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were born because someone wanted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were definitely wanted by someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.88,0:21:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.86,0:22:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.11,0:22:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I just said isn't wrong, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.33,0:22:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.83,0:22:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of expression do I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.50,0:22:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.89,0:22:31.06,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:44.49,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(200,474)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:44.49,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.49,0:22:47.45,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:23:01.13,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:23:01.13,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(193,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.73,0:23:25.99,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:34.41,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.41,0:23:36.87,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
